8 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
to refer to the people for their approval or
9 rejection a proposed amendment to Section 3 of
Article VI of the Constitution of the State of
10 Oklahoma; providing additional eligibility
requirement for the Office of Attorney General;
11 providing ballot title; and directing filing.
12
13
14 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
15 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
16 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
17 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
18 the following proposed amendment to Section 3 of Article VI of the
19 Constitution of the State of Oklahoma to read as follows:
20 Section 3. A. No person shall be eligible to the office of
21 Governor, Lieutenant Governor, Secretary of State, State Auditor and
22 Inspector, Attorney General, State Treasurer, or Superintendent of
23 Public Instruction except a citizen of the United States of the age
24 of not less than thirty-one (31) years and who shall have been ten
ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1070 Page 1

1 (10) years next preceding his or her election, or appointment, a
2 qualified elector of this state.
3 B. In addition to the eligibility requirements in subsection A
4 of this section, no person shall be eligible to the Office of
5 Attorney General except an attorney licensed to practice law in the
6 State of Oklahoma who has been practicing law for at least five (5)
7 years.
8 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
9 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
10 the following form:
11 BALLOT TITLE
12 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
13 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
14 This proposition amends Section 3 of Article 6 of the Oklahoma
15 Constitution. Section 3 provides the eligibility requirements
16 for certain state offices including the Office of Attorney
17 General. This proposition would amend the section to also
18 require that for a person to be eligible to be Attorney General
19 the person must be an attorney licensed to practice law in the
20 State of Oklahoma who has been practicing law for at least five
21 (5) years.
22 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
23 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
24 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1070 Page 2

1 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
2 immediately after the passage of this resolution, shall prepare and
3 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
4 SECTION 2 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
5 Attorney General.
6 Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of March, 2026.
